cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with physical layer security and routing in ad hoc networks, which involves topics such as network protocols, security, information theory, and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the tradeoffs between communication quality of service and transmission security, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper derives closed-form expressions for connection outage probability and secrecy outage probability, which involves information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely category as well. The paper proposes routing algorithms that can achieve optimal performance tradeoffs in a distributed manner, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper presents simulation and numerical results, which involves multimedia and signal processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
